n-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530013\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mot1665702740649.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mot1665702740649.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mot1665702740649.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mot1665702740649\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Monitoring the Uniface Router\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The activities that you can perform with the Uniface Router Monitor depend on whether or not you are a privileged user.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"mot1665702740649__context_N1001A_N10017_N10001\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"mot1665702740649__topic_d31337e1_d31338e1_d31339e1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16034e1_d16035e1_d16036e1\">You must have privileged user status to use\n                  the Uniface Router Monitor to stop and start servers, stop the Uniface Router, and\n                  perform other privileged operations. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rfy1665702740722.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rfy1665702740722.html\" title=\"If you have privileged user status, you can use the Uniface Router Monitor to stop and start Uniface Servers, change Uniface Router settings, change and add Uniface server type (UST) settings, stop the Uniface Router, and reload the Uniface Router’s assignment file.\">Acquire Privileged User Status for the Uniface Router Monitor</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16037e1_d16038e1_d16039e1\">Before starting the Uniface Router Monitor, ensure that the Router Monitor’s assignment file <span class=\"ph filepath\">urmon.asn</span> is located in your installation directory’s <span class=\"ph filepath\">adm</span> subdirectory.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"mot1665702740649__topic_d31340e1_d31341e1_d31342e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mot1665702740649__p_d31343e1_d31344e1_d31345e1\">To use the Uniface Router Monitor:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16040e1_d16041e1_d16042e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mot1665702740649__p_d31346e1_d31347e1_d31348e1\">Start the Uniface Router Monitor. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Urouter &gt;Monitor</span></span>from the Windows <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Start</span> menu.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mot1665702740649__p_d31349e1_d31350e1_d31351e1\">By default, the Connect dialog is displayed, but\n                  this behavior can be altered by editing the monitor settings.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16043e1_d16044e1_d16045e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"reh1665702740792.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/reh1665702740792.html\" title=\"You can connect a single Router Monitor to only one Uniface Router at a time. However, it is possible to have multiple Monitors connected to a single Uniface Router.\">Connect the Uniface Router Monitor to the Uniface Router</a>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16046e1_d16047e1_d16048e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mot1665702740649__p_d31352e1_d31353e1_d31354e1\">Optionally, define and save the connection\n               settings and other preferences. Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File &gt;Settings</span></span>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pls1665702740931.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pls1665702740931.html\" title=\"To control the behavior of the Uniface Router Monitor, you can edit the monitor preferences.\">Specify Preferences for the Uniface Router Monitor</a>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"mot1665702740649__note_N10092_N1008F_N1007A_N1004B_N10017_N10001\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You can define\n                  TCP and TLS connection options in the assignment file of the Uniface Router\n                  Monitor (<span class=\"ph filepath\">urmon.asn</span>).</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16049e1_d16050e1_d16051e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qkt1665702741070.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qkt1665702741070.html\">Monitor the Performance of the Uniface Router</a>\n</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16052e1_d16053e1_d16054e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you want to use the Uniface Router Monitor to start and stop Uniface servers and other tasks, ensure you have privileged user status. This enables you to:\n \n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16055e1_d16056e1_d16057e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lqk1665702741143.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqk1665702741143.html\" title=\"If you are a privileged user, you can use the Uniface Router Monitor to dynamically change the settings for the Uniface Router. In addition, you can set the value of the $IOPRINT assignment setting for the Uniface Router and you can specify the message to be sent to clients or Router Monitors when they are unable to connect to the Uniface Router.\">Change Uniface Router Settings</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16058e1_d16059e1_d16060e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ujg1665702723865.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujg1665702723865.html\" title=\"If you are a privileged user, you can use the Uniface Router Monitor to dynamically create or change a Uniface Server type (UST).\">Define USTs Dynamically</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16061e1_d16062e1_d16063e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fzt1665702718233.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fzt1665702718233.html\" title=\"If you are a privileged user, you can start one or more Uniface Servers from the Router Monitor.\">Start Uniface Servers from the Uniface Router Monitor</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mot1665702740649__li_d16064e1_d16065e1_d16066e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uzp1665702528565.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uzp1665702528565.html\" title=\"If you are a privileged user, you can stop a Uniface Server from the Router Monitor using its Server ID. You can also stop more than one server by specifying matching criteria for servers or matching criteria for clients that are being served.\">Stop Uniface Servers and Routers from the Uniface Router Monitor</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qyk1665702738023.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Router Monitor</a><p>The Uniface Router Monitor is a Uniface Windows application that you can use to fine-tune the performance of the Uniface Router while it is running.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exm1665702529212.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Router</a><p>The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530013\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530013\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Monitoring the Uniface Router Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Monitoring the Uniface Router The activities that you can perform with the Uniface Router Monitor depend on whether or not you are a privileged user. You must have privileged user status to use the Uniface Router Monitor to stop and start servers, stop the Uniface Router, and perform other privileged operations. For more information, see Acquire Privileged User Status for the Uniface Router Monitor . Before starting the Uniface Router Monitor, ensure that the Router Monitor’s assignment file urmon.asn is located in your installation directory’s adm subdirectory. To use the Uniface Router Monitor: Start the Uniface Router Monitor. Choose Urouter >Monitor from the Windows Start menu. By default, the Connect dialog is displayed, but this behavior can be altered by editing the monitor settings. Connect the Uniface Router Monitor to the Uniface Router . Optionally, define and save the connection settings and other preferences. Choose File >Settings . For more information, see Specify Preferences for the Uniface Router Monitor . Note: You can define TCP and TLS connection options in the assignment file of the Uniface Router Monitor ( urmon.asn ). Monitor the Performance of the Uniface Router If you want to use the Uniface Router Monitor to start and stop Uniface servers and other tasks, ensure you have privileged user status. This enables you to: Change Uniface Router Settings Define USTs Dynamically Start Uniface Servers from the Uniface Router Monitor Stop Uniface Servers and Routers from the Uniface Router Monitor Related Links Uniface Router Monitor The Uniface Router Monitor is a Uniface Windows application that you can use to fine-tune the performance of the Uniface Router while it is running. Uniface Router The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}